          <msContents>
            <summary>Rudrayantra, the first section of the manuscript, is a description of a mystic diagram related to Rudra's abode (rudrālaya). Presented as a discourse between the legendary sage Agastya and the Hindu deity Hayagrīva, a horse-headed form of Viṣṇu. Pīṭhadevatā, the second section of the manuscript, is a series of Hindu mantras devoted to and praising various gods, especially to Śiva and his assortment of attendants.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
